OL,3,CYoung musicians plant trees to
OL,4,Ccelebrate 100 years of countryside
OL,5,Cprotection
OL,7,FOne hundred trees have been planted
OL,8,Fnear Pensford to mark the centenary of
OL,9,Fenvironmental charity Campaign to
OL,10,FProtect Rural England (CPRE).
OL,12,FThey were planted by members of
OL,13,FBristol Youth Orchestra who are
OL,14,Fperforming a 'concert for the
OL,15,Fcountryside' at the end of March.
OL,17,FThe charity says it hopes the trees,
OL,18,Fwhich will form part of the Great Avon
OL,19,FWood, will inspire a new generation of
OL,20,Fcountryside custodians.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/5
